@startuml
title ShopSmart — Component & system architecture

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam roundcorner 6

node "Client device" {
  [Browser\nNext.js + React + Axios] as Browser
  note right of Browser
    **Session (cross-origin)**
    Access + refresh JWT in **localStorage**.
    API calls: **Authorization: Bearer**
    Base URL: **NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL**
    (e.g. shopsmart-server.taj.works)
  end note
}

cloud "Frontend host\n(e.g. shopsmart.taj.works)" {
  [Next.js App Router\nSSR / SSG / client navigation] as NextApp
}

node "API host\n(e.g. shopsmart-server.taj.works)" {
  package "Express application" {
    [HTTP surface\n/api/** and /api-docs/**] as HttpSurface
    [Middleware\n(CORS, helmet, rate limit, JSON)] as Middleware
    [authenticate / authorize\n(JWT Bearer + RBAC)] as AuthLayer
    [Feature controllers\n(modules)] as Controllers
    [Business services] as Services
    [Factories + DI container] as DIContainer
    [Prisma repositories] as Repositories
  }
}

database "PostgreSQL\n(managed)" {
  [Primary + optional replicas] as Postgres
}

cloud "External integrations" {
  [Email provider\nNodemailer / SendGrid] as EmailProvider
}

' --- User traffic ---
Browser --> NextApp : **HTTPS**\nHTML, JS, assets, SSR

' --- Cross-origin API (primary integration path) ---
Browser --> HttpSurface : **HTTPS** JSON **REST**\n**CORS** (FRONTEND_URL)\n**Bearer** token

' --- Optional: Next.js server calls API (RSC, route handlers, etc.) ---
NextApp ..> HttpSurface : **HTTPS** optional\nserver-side **fetch**

' --- In-process API pipeline ---
HttpSurface --> Middleware
Middleware --> AuthLayer
AuthLayer --> Controllers
Controllers --> Services
Services <--> Repositories : domain I/O
DIContainer ..> Services : inject
DIContainer ..> Controllers : inject
Repositories <--> Postgres : **Prisma**\nTCP/TLS

Services --> EmailProvider : transactional mail\n(verify, reset, …)

note bottom of HttpSurface
  **Swagger UI** is served from the same Express
  app (**/api-docs**). OpenAPI **Try it out**
  targets the configured API server URL.
end note

note bottom of NextApp
  Frontend and API are **separate deployables**
  on different origins; the browser is the
  integration point for authenticated **REST**.
end note

@enduml
